      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JEKYLL AND HYDE (1) placed on debut by one length (18.60) at Richmond over 320m. Draws the cherry. Should be further improved and rates on top this time. LAINEY BANNER (4) trailed the lead and fought on well to be beaten 8 lengths into third (19.27) at Richmond in a Maiden over 320m. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Must be included in calculations. KALIMERA (6) turned in a moderate run last time when fifth at Maitland over 400m behind Borrowed Times (23.05) in a Maiden. Placed at his previous run. Has good early speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. MELLCAT EXPRESS (2) is a newcomer from the John Mellon kennel. Drawn favourably and can capitalise. Profiles nicely and can feature in the finish.",
